FBIS4-35101 "drlat125_k_94001" FBIS-LAT-94-125 Daily Report 28 Jun 1994 SOUTH AMERICA Argentina CNEA Head Denies Construction of Nuclear Plant CNEA Head Denies Construction of Nuclear Plant PY2806200594 Buenos Aires NOTICIAS ARGENTINAS in Spanish 1250 GMT 28 Jun 94 PY2806200594 Buenos Aires NOTICIAS ARGENTINAS Spanish BFN [Text] Cordoba, 28 Jun (NA) -- Manuel Mondino, the National Commission for Atomic Energy [CNEA] chairman, has denied that the construction of a new nuclear power plant in Cordoba is being reconsidered and holds journalists responsible for disseminating inaccurate reports on this issue. The CNEA chairman categorically stressed that "no decision has been made." He added that "a decision may be made by the end of the year, if it is made at all." Mondino was very angry with journalists. He stressed that neither "the National Government, the CNEA, nor anyone else has ever discussed the construction of a second nuclear power plant." Mondino described as "nonsense" reports released during President Carlos Menem's visit to Canada, where Menem addressed the issue.
